Tourism organization. Products/services and target groups at the internship organization. Customer group analysis. Product marketing messages and channels. Persona. Mapping the customer journey. Mapping competitors. SWOT analysis. The value proposition of the organization. Development proposals. Description of tasks and assignments. Self-analysis as an intern and as the author of the internship report. Correct use of professional vocabulary. Finding and using relevant sources of information. Preparation of the internship report. Defence of the report.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide students with deeper theoretical knowledge and allow them to obtain practical experience in a tourism organization, including product development and marketing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) explains the principles of operation of their internship organization and the theoretical approaches of organizations; 2) analyzes the products and services of the internship organization, and their suitability for a specific customer group; 3) analyzes the tourism organization's product development and marketing strategies; 4) compiles the value proposition of the organization for a chosen customer group; 5) analyzes their own performance regarding their tasks and assignments; 6) uses the correct professional vocabulary and relevant sources of information during their internship at the organization and when compiling the internship report.
